     <tbody>\\n                <tr class=\"replica\" name=\"intro_txt\">\\n                 <td align=\"left\" class=\"dm-text\" style=\"padding-bottom: 20px;\">\\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 20px; line-height: 28px; font-family: \\'Helvetica Neue\\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">\\n                   <b>\\n                    Biden Backup Plans, CNN\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Debate Hangover, A Picasso Surprise\\n                   </b>\\n                  </p>\\n                 </td>\\n                </tr>\\n                <tr class=\"replica\" name=\"intro_txt\">\\n                 <td align=\"left\" class=\"dm-text\" style=\"padding-bottom: 34px;\">\\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28px; font-family: \\'Helvetica Neue\\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">\\n                   Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon guide to the best new work at Puck.\\n                   <br/>\\n                   <br/>\\n                   Today, we lead with\\n                   <b>\\n                    Dylan Byers\\n                   </b>\\n                   \\xe2\\x80\\x99 double-barreled reporting on the two biggest stories preoccupying the Washington media: the latest beats in the\\n                   <i>\\n                    Washington Post\\n                   </i>\\n                   crisis and the postmortem on CNN\\xe2\\x80\\x99s ratings bonanza in Atlanta.\\n                   <br/>\\n                   <br/>\\n                   Plus, below the fold:\\n                   <b>\\n                    Bill Cohan\\n                   </b>\\n                   examines Goldman\\xe2\\x80\\x99s new rainmaker and a potential M&amp;A plot twist in\\n                   <b>\\n                    Zaslav\\n                   </b>\\n                   \\xe2\\x80\\x99s Hollywood story.\\n                   <b>\\n                    Marion Maneker\\n                   </b>\\n       