align=\"left\" class=\"dm-text\" style=\"padding-bottom: 10px;\">\\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; font-family: \\'Helvetica Neue\\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 700;\">\\n                   MARION MANEKER\\n                  </p>\\n                 </td>\\n                </tr>\\n                <tr class=\"replica\" name=\"story3_text\">\\n                 <td align=\"left\" class=\"dm-text\" style=\"padding-bottom: 26px;border-bottom: 1px solid #D9D9D9;\">\\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: \\'Helvetica Neue\\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">\\n                   The June sales in London are in the midst of being downgraded. But that doesn\\xe2\\x80\\x99t mean we can\\xe2\\x80\\x99t learn a thing or two from the tepid results, which show the market is still bottoming. Plus, a preview of the Old Master sales.\\n                  </p>\\n                 </td>\\n                </tr>\\n                <!-- -->\\n                <!-- -->\\n                <tr class=\"replica\" name=\"story4_image\">\\n                 <td align=\"center\" style=\"padding-bottom: 10px; padding-top: 34px;\">\\n                  <a href=\"https://email.puck.\" target=\"_blank\">\\n                   <img alt=\"\" class=\"w100pct\" src=\"https://images.scalero.io/email_assets/2602/XSP0ZLGTKHR13YMFDI2D614KLQUDE91MAZZRAA9OECMFDJED9LOV800WJKCCXZPY.jpg\" style=\"width:540px;border: 0;\" width=\"540\"/>\\n                  </a>\\n                 </td>\\n                </tr>\\n                <tr class=\"replica\" name=\"story4_title\">\\n                 <td align=\"left\" style=\"padding-bottom: 10px;\">\\n                  <a href=\"https://email.puck.\" target=\"_blank\">\\n                   <p style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 30px; line-height: 36px; color: #D40000; font-family: Beskerville, Georgia, \\'Times New Roman\\', Times, serif;\">\\n                    Will the Debate Debacle Revive TV News?\\n                   </p>\\n                  </a>\\n                 </td>\\n                </tr>\\n                <tr class=\"replica\" name=\"story4_author\">\\n                 <td align=\"left\" class=\"dm-text\" style=\"padding-bottom: 10px;\">\\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; font-family: \\'Helvetica Neue\\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 700;\">\\n                   MATTHEW BELLONI\\n                  </p>\\n                 </td>\\n                </tr>\\n                <tr class=\"replica\" name=\"story4_text\">\\n                 <td align=\"left\" class=\"dm-text\" style=\"padding-bottom: 26px;border-bottom: 1px solid #D9D9D9;\">\\n                  <p style=\"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; font-family: \\'Helvetica Neue\\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">\\n                   Matt is joined by Semafor cofounder Ben Smith to discuss how the dispiriting presidential debate will affect CNN and the TV news landscape as we move towards the 2024 election. They also take a look at the broader state of TV news as we exit the cable news era and wonder how many of these waning news networks can survive in the streaming era.\\n                  </p>\\n                 </td>\\n                </tr>\\n                <!-- -->\\n               </tbody>\\n              </table>\\n             </td>\\n            </tr>\\n            <!-- END OF S4 -->\\n            <!-- S5 -->\\n            <tr>\\n             <td align=\"center\" class=\"padL12 padR12\" style=\"padding-top: 34px;\">\\n              <table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"w100pct\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"width: 540px;\" width=\"540\">\\n               <!-- -->\\n               <tbody>\\n                <tr class=\"replica\" name=\"story5_image\">\\n                 <td align=\"center\" style=\"padding-bot